        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 2:14PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Day Center, or 16 miles northwest of Saratoga Springs, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thurman Station, Big Hollow, Beartown, Lake Luzerne, Fourth Lake,
Lake George, Conklingville, Stony Creek Station, Athol, Brayton, Lake
Luzerne-Hadley, Lake Luzerne Campground, West Day, Batchellerville,
Fox Hill, Allentown, Day Center, Edinburg, Mount Pleasant, and
Knowelhurst.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 21 and 22.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
